\end{results}

\begin{conclusion}
There is a positive correlation between the budget for TV advertising and Sales; however, this relationship is very minimal. For every $1,000 spent on advertising only another \Sexpr{ad_summ$coefficients[2]*1000} units are sold, so each unit would have to cost at least \Sexpr{round(1000/(ad_summ$coefficients[2]*1000), 2)} in order to break even or profit off the units sold. 
\end{conclusion}

